cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.SI 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a framework for deploying machine learning models when only little or no training data is initially available. It also uses a full Bayesian Deep Latent Gaussian Model (BELGAM) with a novel inference method, which is a popular approach in the field of machine learning. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with the challenge of training an AI system for predicting patient metrics from lab tests. 

The paper may also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it mentions real-world recommender systems and health-care applications, which may involve image and text data. 

Finally, it may belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as recommender systems are often used in social networks to suggest friends or content to users.
